text: If you're looking for a chill spot to sing some karaoke and have a few beers, this KTV pub is the place to be. Beers are reasonably priced, so you can enjoy without breaking the bank. Big shoutout to Alvis who took great care of us and our friends.
Massive subwoofer hum coming from the faulty audio equipment, the main TV screen needs to be replaced as there are lines running through it, especially due to the fact it's a karaoke ðŸŽ¤ bar

Drinks at affordable price in a cozy environment. Beers are generally more popular here instead of spirits (mostly Japanese spirits) as they usually have great promos for beers.

The Thai-styled Moo Ping finger food was amazing and reasonably priced.  Recommend ordering it when you're here!

Good food. Pork chops are a must try. Wings as well. They serve Australian beer, Tooheys, no headaches the next day. Prompt and friendly staff, knowledgeable with drinking games. Love the local munchies they serve that goes complimentary with the beer.
Good and chill KTV bar with a relatively younger crowd.
